</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F25><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukronx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kronx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/4/01 4:59:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild war anyone?</span><hr size=1> Okay, sounds fun. Our leader is Caluha. I don't think I've even mentioned it to him yet, but just tell him Kronx was asking if anyone would consider the possibility.<br>
<br>
If a guild war is too complicated, we could all meet at a PvP place in force and jump in at once.<br>
<br>
I'm just trying to do anything that isn't a raid and might prove interesting.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usubo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Subo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dwarfus Stoutus</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/4/01 5:19:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild war anyone?</span><hr size=1> I believe death by proc or pet or bleeding to death are still considered environmental deaths and result in exp loss. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F25><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grumpy Ol' Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/4/01 6:31:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild war anyone?</span><hr size=1> You could always just meet in the arena as well.  Makes AE use a bit more interesting, as you can hit your teammates... but if one big battle on the plains is what you are looking for, it should do the trick. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uverbalsabre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Verbalsabre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://verbalsabre.50megs.com/images/lsabre.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/4/01 9:22:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild war anyone?</span><hr size=1> Have done a guildwar in WC and it was a blast. I cannot remember the exact commands but yes it can be started and stoped at will but requires both guild leaders to enter the appropriate command. <br>
<br>
Definitely do this in a zone and not the arena. The feeling I got as I was running along and a group of 6 rose up out of the lake to ambush me was priceless.  <p><center><font size="-1"><p><i><b><a href="http://verbalsabre.50megs.com">Sabre</b></i></a></font><br>54 Channeler<br><a href="http://www.phoenixhorizon.com">Phoenix Horizon</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F25><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/unurrse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nurrse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/5/01 8:54:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild war anyone?</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
I remember that Guild War, set up took forever but it was a lot of fun. WC was a decent place to have it at the time too. I remember my druid charming a kodiak and sending it after Dragus I think, while the rest of us chased him down (Tooten was there too, don't remember who else). Was a lot of fun! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umuuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(10/5/01 9:21:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild war anyone?</span><hr size=1> Guild-war! Guild-war! Guild-WAR! GUILD-WAR! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
